<body>
  <div class="wrap">
    <header>
      <div>
        <h1>Blackened Grilled Salmon Feast</h1>
        <div class="sub">Blackened salmon + creamy dill sauce + rice pilaf + grilled asparagus. Built for balanced flavor and texture.</div>
      </div>
      <nav class="meta">
        <a href="/">Home</a>
        <a href="/blog/">Blog</a>
      </nav>
    </header>

    <hr />

    <h2>Blackened seasoning</h2>
    <div class="card">
      <div class="meta">Mix and keep in a jar. Great on salmon, chicken, and vegetables.</div>
      <ul>
        <li>3 tbsp paprika</li>
        <li>2 tbsp kosher salt</li>
        <li>2 tbsp garlic powder</li>
        <li>1 tbsp black pepper</li>
        <li>1 tbsp white pepper</li>
        <li>1 tbsp onion powder</li>
        <li>1 tbsp dried oregano</li>
        <li>1 tbsp cayenne pepper (adjust to taste)</li>
        <li>1/2 tbsp dried thyme</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <h2>Blackened grilled salmon</h2>
    <div class="card">
      <ol>
        <li>Combine the spices to make the seasoning mix.</li>
        <li>Pat salmon fillets dry and coat with seasoning.</li>
        <li>Preheat grill to medium-high and cook salmon about 4–5 minutes per side, to medium or medium-well.</li>
      </ol>
      <p class="meta" style="margin-bottom:0;">Tip from the draft: a good spray of oil on the grill (and a little on the fish) helps prevent sticking.</p>
    </div>

    <h2>Creamy dill sauce</h2>
    <div class="two">
      <div class="card">
        <h3 style="margin-top:0;">Ingredients</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>1/2 cup sour cream</li>
          <li>1/3 cup mayonnaise</li>
          <li>2 tbsp butter</li>
          <li>2 cloves garlic, minced</li>
          <li>1/4 cup finely chopped onion</li>
          <li>2 tbsp chopped fresh dill</li>
          <li>1 tbsp fresh lemon juice</li>
          <li>Salt and pepper to taste</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <h3 style="margin-top:0;">Directions</h3>
        <ol>
          <li>Melt butter over medium heat; sauté garlic + onion until onion is translucent.</li>
          <li>Stir in sour cream and mayo; heat gently to combine (don’t boil).</li>
          <li>Remove from heat; stir in dill + lemon. Season to taste.</li>
        </ol>
      </div>
    </div>

    <h2>Rice pilaf</h2>
    <div class="two">
      <div class="card">
        <h3 style="margin-top:0;">Ingredients</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>1 cup long-grain rice</li>
          <li>2 tbsp butter</li>
          <li>2 cloves garlic, minced</li>
          <li>1/4 cup finely chopped onion</li>
          <li>1/4 cup finely chopped celery</li>
          <li>1/4 cup finely chopped carrot</li>
          <li>2 cups chicken stock</li>
          <li>2 tbsp chopped fresh dill</li>
          <li>Salt and pepper to taste</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <h3 style="margin-top:0;">Directions</h3>
        <ol>
          <li>Melt butter; sauté garlic, onion, celery, carrot until softened.</li>
          <li>Add rice; sauté briefly to coat.</li>
          <li>Add chicken stock; bring to boil, reduce heat, cover, simmer 15–20 min until absorbed.</li>
          <li>Stir in dill; season to taste.</li>
        </ol>
      </div>
    </div>

    <h2>Grilled asparagus</h2>
    <div class="card">
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Ingredients:</strong> asparagus, olive oil, salt, pepper</li>
      </ul>
      <ol>
        <li>Blanch briefly in boiling water, then shock in ice water.</li>
        <li>Drizzle with olive oil; season with salt and pepper.</li>
        <li>Grill 2–4 minutes per side.</li>
      </ol>
    </div>

    <footer style="margin-top:44px;color:#666;font-size:14px;">
